<h1>Introduction</h1>
<p><em>Sankat Mochan Ashtakam</em> is a song or poem which is sung in the praise of Lord Hanuman.</p>
<p>It has a famous refrain as follows:</p>
<pre><code>को नहीं जानत है जग में कपि,
संकटमोचन नाम तिहारो 
</code></pre>
<p>
<em>
Ko Nahi Jaanat Hai Jag Mein Kapi,
<br />
Sankatmochan Naam Tiharo
</em>
</p>
<p>which roughly translates to:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>
Who in this world doesn't know, "Your name is Sankatmochan (Problem Solver)"
</p>
</blockquote>
<h2 id="story">Preface <a class="direct-link" href="#story">#</a></h2>
<p>An <em>Ashtakam</em> (अष्टकम् aṣṭakam)) is a poetic composition with eight verses or paragraphs, which is normally sung to praise a God.</p>
<p>Lord Hanuman is a devotee of Lord Ram and is famous for solving all of problems of whoever requests him.</p>
<p>
He is also known as '<em>Sankat Mochan</em>' which means 'Problem Solver' in Sanskrit or Hindi. This <em>ashtakam</em> is a request to Him to solve our problems.
</p>
<p>
This website is divided into eight chapters, each related to one verse of <em>Sankat Mochan ashtakam</em>. Each Chapter has one or more stories related to each verse or stanza of this holy poem.
</p>

